Introduced: <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260106010559/http://www.theregister.co.uk/2011/03/28/arista_7050s_7124sx_switches/">March 28 2011</a> in <i>The Register</i>
<p>
The Trident+ has a 9 MByte block of packet buffer which is partitioned 
by the switch software between dedicated per-port buffers and a 
dynamic buffer pool that can be allocated on demand.  Arista
calls this <b>DBA.</b>
For the Arista 7050S, we know that this was tested and reported in 
the <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260106010559/http://www.aristanetworks.com/media/system/pdf/LippisTestReportMay2011.pdf"> Spring 2011 Lippis Report</a>. See page 31.
<p>
Most recent <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260106010559/https://people.ucsc.edu/~warner/Bufs/7050S_Datasheet.pdf">data sheet</a> 
<p>
--------------------------------------------------
<p>
The 7050S family has reached <b>End of Life</b>. This was announced
in Februrary 2016 with a final sales date of August 2016.
